LOKOJA – The President, Enemona Foundation, Gabriel Enemona, has assured the youths and vulnerable of his commitment to assist in finding decent sources of livelihoods that will take them off the streets. He noted that it is only when concerted efforts by all stakeholders in Nigeria project to ensure the youths finds meaningful sources of living , that insecurity facing the society would be brought to a halt. The President whose mission is to eradicate poverty and eliminate all forms of crimes and criminality associated with the youth, also as the zonal Chairman of solid mineral buyers and transporters Association, disclosed this on Saturday at Ejule in ofu Local Government Area of kogi during the stakeholders sensitisation for small scale and artisanal miners in kogi East zone of the state. Move Beyond Ambition To Action, Urges ILO Director-General U.S. Consulate Supports Mentoring Programme For 125 Young… He explained that, his joy knows no limit when he sees young persons, widows, vulnerable are given impetus to advance their God given potentials. He said: “it was an attempt to assist this group of Nigerians that the Enemona Foundation was established to give lifelines to communities, young persons and women through its numerous life changing programmes being executed by the foundation. Enemona who bemoaned the parlous economic realities facing the youth which have drawn them into unwholesome behaviours, stressing that equipping them with wherewithal will drastically reduce crime and criminality that has bedeviled the country. He added that having studied the policy of the present government in solid mineral development, through small scale and artisanal mining, he has to seize the opportunity by organising the youths to participate in this sector that can bring enormous prosperity to them.